news.title: Pune: PMC sealing civic properties over rent dues in fresh drive
news.para: At least 27 such commercial properties have already been sealed to recover dues worth Rs3.5 crore. According to PMC data, it has over 3,700 properties that have been given out on rent across city localities.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC to revamp three housing complexes
news.para: To begin with, NDMC has finalised a scheme for repairing houses and common areas in three societies for municipal sanitation staff — Balmiki Basti housing complex (Mandir Marg), costing Rs.7.5 crore; Palika Dham Housing Complex, Gole Market (Rs 4.5 crore); and housing Complex Bapu Dham, Chanakyapuri (Rs 1 crore).

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to dispose of 200 properties worth over Rs 200 crore
news.para: The move comes in the wake of the decision of the Chandigarh administration to convert leasehold properties of all departments and UT authorities for their proper disposal.

news.title: Sagar Cements surges 8% as board okays issuance of shares to Premji Invest affiliate
news.para: The company’s scrip surged to a high of Rs 275 as against Rs 254.85 at previous close on the National Stock Exchange. The stock was last trading 3 per cent higher.

news.title: Pune civic body eyes revenue from Metro assets by charging property tax
news.para: The civic body is eying revenue generation from Metro stations and pillars, by charging property tax at commercial rates.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 5 lakh properties into tax net
news.para: The property tax department of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) brought 4,000 new properties into the tax net in the last 40 days.

news.title: About 48 ready-to-move-in flats to be allotted in Greater Noida
news.para: These are ready-to-move-in one, two and three BHK flats located in Sector Omicron 1 & 1 A, MU 2, XU 3, Eta 2 and Sector 12. The houses are in the range of Rs 9 lakh to Rs 73 lakh – with varied prices according to the sector.

news.title: Two benches functioning, MahaRERA cases pile up
news.para: According to MahaRERA website, as many as 16,478 complaints have been registered with the state’s real estate authority. Of these, orders have been passed only in 11,662 cases, while the remaining are still in the process.

news.title: DLF to invest Rs 2,000 crore to build two shopping malls in Gurugram, Goa
news.para: At present, DLF has a retail footprint of 42 lakh square feet comprising eight properties, including malls and shopping centres, mainly across Delhi-NCR.

news.title: India Sotheby's International Realty invests Rs 5.5 crore in CRE Matrix
news.para: Abhishek Kiran Gupta, CEO and co-founder, CRE Matrix, told PTI, "We have raised Rs 5.5 crore from India Sotheby's International Realty. We had earlier raised Rs 2 crore from angel investors".

news.title: Godrej Properties to develop 33-acre project in Bengaluru
news.para: The new project of Godrej Properties has a developable potential of approximately 3.4 million sq ft of saleable area with an estimated revenue of approximately Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: Income tax raids at premises linked to Hiranandani group concludes
news.para: “We have fully cooperated with the authorities and handed over everything that they asked from us. We find that the department entrusted with information gathering had differing opinions of tax treatments on various transactions. We shall suitably address any issues and conclusions drawn once finalized by the tax department and respond accordingly,” a Hiranandani spokesperson said in a statement.

news.title: Delhi government set aside Rs 1,300 crore to provide basic amenities to unauthorised colonies
news.para: Chief minister Arvind Kejriwal said that except a few colonies that were yet to be regularised, all other colonies would have water pipelines, sewer network, roads and drainage connectivity within a year.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body wing told to get its act together on illegal buildings
news.para: ​He has already submitted a report to the local bodies department on illegal buildings and there are chances that the government might issue a chargesheet against the officials whose names were mentioned in the report.

news.title: Lucknow development body razes, seals illegal structures in city areas
news.para: The enforcement wing of LDA demolished illegal construction in Khojoli market in Gosainganj, while structure erected at Hanuman Mandir in Aminabad was sealed by it.
